SWIG INSTALL

Download the last SWIG library on http://www.swig.org
Version tested: swig-1.3.39
Compile it and install it on your computer.



SWIG USAGE


Manual Python binding with swig on Linux:
   $ cd binding/python
   $ swig -c++ -python -o libgexf_wrap.cpp libgexf.i
   $ gcc -fPIC -c libgexf_wrap.cpp ../../graph.cpp ../../gexf.cpp -I/usr/include/python2.5
   $ g++ -shared libgexf_wrap.o graph.o gexf.o -o _libgexf.so

Automated Python binding with swig on Linux:
   $ cd binding/python
   $ swig -c++ -python -o libgexf_wrap.cpp libgexf.i
   $ python setup.py build


To use :
   $ python
    >>> import libgexf
    >>> from libgexf import *
    >>> g = GEXF()
   ...

To install:
   $ sudo python setup.py install

to build
    $ python setup.py build
   
to distribute
    $ python setup.py sdist
    
    


Limitations:
   * friend functions are ignored
   * new, delete, assignment and conversion operators are ignored...in general, do not overload 
operators!
   * prefer avoid functions with variable arguments
